stylometry: Simulation models allow you to work with several unknowns. It takes your output and creates numbers for the inputs that you do not know making the outputs a function of the inputs. It is a quick and easy process to change a process or a model to see what would happen with the numbers without actually changing the process physically for a company. Simulation models also help show the degree to which factors contribute to your output. For example some inputs may not greatly effect your output, a simulation model helps recognize this as well.
